# cite-citadel workspace configuration — auto-loaded from the workspace root (no python-dotenv).
# This top section is all most setups need. Everything below the "Advanced" line is optional
# tuning: the defaults are right for most workspaces, and `citadel doctor` flags misconfiguration.
#
# No API key needed: ingest shells out to a coding-agent CLI you are already logged in to, under
# your own account and your provider's terms — see the README "License & third-party tools"
# section. Full per-knob reference: docs/configuration.md.

# Which CLI ingest shells out to, run AGENTICALLY (autonomous file tools): claude | copilot | gemini.
CITADEL_LLM_CLI=claude

# Model for the claude backend — an alias (sonnet | opus | haiku) or a full id; copilot/gemini use their own.
CITADEL_INGEST_MODEL=sonnet

# Per-session CLI timeout in seconds; raise it for opus or large raw files.
# CITADEL_LLM_TIMEOUT=1200

# Target language of ALL wiki prose, whatever the sources' languages (verbatim quotes stay original).
# CITADEL_WIKI_LANG=en

# Write one transcript per source (prompt + full CLI output) here; relative = under the workspace root.
# CITADEL_LLM_LOG_DIR=.citadel_llm_logs

# ============================== Advanced (optional) ==============================
# Long-form explanations for every knob below — plus the "Local models (Ollama)" recipes for
# running ingest fully on your own machine or LAN — live in docs/configuration.md.

# --- Paths & multi-root ---
# Relative values resolve against the WORKSPACE ROOT; absolute values may point outside it (e.g. a
# mounted network drive — out-of-workspace sources are keyed by absolute path and fully supported).
# Wiki and raw work best under a common parent or with both roots configured explicitly;
# `citadel doctor` checks that citation links actually resolve ("workspace coherence").
# CITADEL_WIKI_DIR=wiki
# CITADEL_RAW_DIR=raw
# CITADEL_DOCS_DIR=docs
# Multiple raw roots: a comma/newline list, each walked by ingest. When set it REPLACES the walk
# list (include `raw` to keep the workspace root); CITADEL_RAW_DIR stays the primary root.
# CITADEL_RAW_DIRS=raw, /mnt/share/dept-docs

# --- Formats: images, PDF, audio, Office dedup ---
# Read image files visually instead of rejecting them as binary; 0 keeps images out of the wiki.
# CITADEL_IMAGE_SUPPORT=1
# PDF mode: text | images — "images" also reads figures/charts (needs a backend that renders PDFs).
# CITADEL_PDF_MODE=text
# Transcribe audio/video files (.mp3/.wav/.m4a/.mp4/...) with a LOCAL whisper-class CLI and ingest
# the [HH:MM:SS]-stamped transcript (cached in .citadel_transcripts/ next to the wiki); needs the
# binary below installed. Off by default.
# CITADEL_AUDIO_SUPPORT=0
# The whisper-class binary — a PATH name or absolute path. Must speak the openai-whisper flags
# (`<file> --output_format srt --output_dir <dir>`; whisper-ctranslate2 / mlx_whisper are
# drop-in compatible) — docs/configuration.md "Audio/video sources".
# CITADEL_WHISPER_CLI=whisper
# Optional model passed as `--model` (e.g. turbo | small | large-v3); empty = the CLI's default.
# CITADEL_WHISPER_MODEL=
# Per-file transcription timeout in seconds (CPU transcription of a long recording is slow).
# CITADEL_WHISPER_TIMEOUT=3600
# Same-folder document exports sharing a basename (report.pptx + report.pdf): ingest only ONE
# (PDF first, then modern Office, then legacy); 0 ingests every format separately.
# CITADEL_DEDUP_BY_BASENAME=1

# --- Large sources & repos ---
# A source longer than this many chars is folded in over several merging passes; 0 disables chunking.
# CITADEL_MAX_SOURCE_CHARS=300000
# A raw/ sub-folder that is a git checkout (or carries a .citadelsource marker) is ingested as ONE
# size-capped digest tracked by its HEAD commit; 0 falls back to the per-file walk.
# CITADEL_REPO_SUPPORT=1
# Repo digest tuning: total character budget, and the per-file cap inside it.
# CITADEL_REPO_DIGEST_MAX_CHARS=120000
# CITADEL_REPO_PER_FILE_MAX_CHARS=8000

# --- Wiki history (git) ---
# Commit the wiki dir after every run that changed it: auto = only when wiki/ is already its own
# git repo, 1 = also `git init` it on first use, 0 = never. Best-effort — never fails a run.
# CITADEL_WIKI_GIT=auto
# Optional push target after each commit — a remote name (origin) or URL; empty = commit locally only.
# CITADEL_WIKI_GIT_REMOTE=git@github.com:you/my-wiki.git

# --- Curate ---
# Model for `citadel curate` sessions (often cheaper than ingest); unset reuses CITADEL_INGEST_MODEL.
# CITADEL_CURATE_MODEL=haiku

# --- Observability ---
# Stream each agent session's output live (the claude CLI prints only its final result envelope —
# use CITADEL_LLM_LOG_DIR above for a full claude record). CLI flag: -v.
# CITADEL_LLM_VERBOSE=0

# --- Ignore patterns ---
# OS/junk globs skipped at discovery (Thumbs.db, .DS_Store, ~$ locks, swap/backup files, ...).
# A comma/newline list REPLACES the built-in defaults; a `+` prefix ADDS to them.
# CITADEL_IGNORE_PATTERNS=+*.bak,~backup*

# --- Style profiles ---
# When 1, first-person sources also yield attributed, dated, cited opinions plus a per-person
# writing-style profile; leave off for many-person corpora.
# CITADEL_STYLE_PROFILES=0

# --- Binary overrides ---
# Override a CLI binary's path when it is not on PATH.
# CLAUDE_CODE_PATH=/home/you/.local/bin/claude
# COPILOT_CLI_PATH=/home/you/.local/bin/copilot
# GEMINI_CLI_PATH=/home/you/.npm-global/bin/gemini
# COPILOT_MODEL / GEMINI_MODEL name the concrete model recorded per source for those backends (for
# copilot it is also the model selector) — docs/configuration.md "Backend selection".
